{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":598,"text":"Pat Mitchell: Your first time back on the TEDWomen stage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":3271,"text":"Sheryl Sandberg: First time back. Nice to see everyone. It's always so nice to look out"},{"time":6214,"text":"and see so many women."},{"time":8132,"text":"It's so not my regular experience, \nas I know anyone else's."}]},{"cues":[{"time":13262,"text":"PM: So when we first started talking about, maybe the subject wouldn't be social media,"},{"time":18654,"text":"which we assumed it would be, but \nthat you had very much on your mind"},{"time":23310,"text":"the missing leadership positions, particularly \nin the sector of technology and social media."},{"time":30464,"text":"But how did that evolve for you as a thought, and end up being the TED Talk that you gave?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":37238,"text":"SS: So I was really scared to get on \nthis stage and talk about women,"},{"time":39809,"text":"because I grew up in the business \nworld, as I think so many of us did."},{"time":43461,"text":"You never talk about being a woman, because \nsomeone might notice that you're a woman, right?"},{"time":49793,"text":"They might notice. Or worse, if you say \"woman,\" \npeople on the other end of the table"},{"time":53953,"text":"think you're asking for special \ntreatment, or complaining."},{"time":57043,"text":"Or worse, about to sue them. \nAnd so I went through -- (Laughter)"},{"time":60751,"text":"Right? I went through my entire business career,"},{"time":62929,"text":"and never spoke about being a woman, \nnever spoke about it publicly."},{"time":66557,"text":"But I also had noticed that it wasn't working."}]},{"cues":[{"time":69460,"text":"I came out of college over \n20 years ago, and I thought"},{"time":72899,"text":"that all of my peers were men and women, \nall the people above me were all men,"},{"time":76798,"text":"but that would change,"},{"time":77896,"text":"because your generation had done such \nan amazing job fighting for equality,"},{"time":82429,"text":"equality was now ours for the taking. And it wasn't."},{"time":86041,"text":"Because year after year, I was one of fewer and fewer,"},{"time":89376,"text":"and now, often the only woman in a room."},{"time":91328,"text":"And I talked to a bunch of people about,"},{"time":93418,"text":"should I give a speech at TEDWomen \nabout women, and they said, oh no, no."},{"time":96839,"text":"It will end your business career. You \ncannot be a serious business executive"},{"time":102033,"text":"and speak about being a woman. \nYou'll never be taken seriously again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":105471,"text":"But fortunately, there were the few, the proud -- like you -- who told me I should give the speech,"},{"time":110346,"text":"and I asked myself the question \nMark Zuckerberg might --"},{"time":113002,"text":"the founder of Facebook and my boss --"},{"time":114840,"text":"asks all of us, which is, what \nwould I do if I wasn't afraid?"},{"time":119419,"text":"And the answer to what would I do if I wasn't \nafraid is I would get on the TED stage,"},{"time":123241,"text":"and talk about women, and leadership. \nAnd I did, and survived. (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":130746,"text":"PM: I would say, not only survived. \nI'm thinking of that moment, Sheryl,"},{"time":134581,"text":"when you and I were standing backstage \ntogether, and you turned to me,"},{"time":138914,"text":"and you told me a story."},{"time":140652,"text":"And I said -- very last minute -- you know, \nyou really should share that story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":144531,"text":"SS: Oh, yeah.\nPM: What was that story?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":146281,"text":"SS: Well, it's an important part of the \njourney. So I had -- TEDWomen --"},{"time":149546,"text":"the original one was in D.C. -- so I live here, \nso I had gotten on a plane the day before,"},{"time":153355,"text":"and my daughter was three, she was \nclinging to my leg: \"Mommy, don't go.\""},{"time":158404,"text":"And Pat's a friend, and so, not related \nto the speech I was planning on giving,"},{"time":162137,"text":"which was chock full of facts and \nfigures, and nothing personal,"},{"time":166599,"text":"I told Pat the story. I said, well, \nI'm having a hard day."},{"time":168865,"text":"Yesterday my daughter was clinging \nto my leg, and \"Don't go.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":171469,"text":"And you looked at me and said, \nyou have to tell that story."},{"time":173213,"text":"I said, on the TED stage? Are you kidding?"},{"time":177448,"text":"I'm going to get on a stage and admit \nmy daughter was clinging to my leg?"},{"time":179905,"text":"And you said yes, because if you want to talk \nabout getting more women into leadership roles,"},{"time":184072,"text":"you have to be honest about how hard it is."},{"time":187209,"text":"And I did. And I think that's a really \nimportant part of the journey."}]},{"cues":[{"time":191945,"text":"The same thing happened when I wrote my book. \nI started writing the book. I wrote a first chapter,"},{"time":197243,"text":"I thought it was fabulous. It was \nchock-full of data and figures,"},{"time":201209,"text":"I had three pages on matrilineal Maasai \ntribes, and their sociological patterns."},{"time":209069,"text":"My husband read it and he was like, this \nis like eating your Wheaties. (Laughter)"},{"time":214132,"text":"No one -- and I apologize to Wheaties if there's \nsomeone -- no one, no one will read this book."},{"time":221497,"text":"And I realized through the process that I \nhad to be more honest and more open,"},{"time":225682,"text":"and I had to tell my stories. My stories of still \nnot feeling as self-confident as I should,"},{"time":230428,"text":"in many situations. My first and \nfailed marriage. Crying at work."},{"time":236647,"text":"Felling like I didn't belong there, \nfeeling guilty to this day."},{"time":240319,"text":"And part of my journey, starting on this stage, \ngoing to \"Lean In,\" going to the foundation,"},{"time":244714,"text":"is all about being more open and \nhonest about those challenges,"},{"time":248602,"text":"so that other women can be more open and honest,"},{"time":250610,"text":"and all of us can work together towards real equality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":254242,"text":"PM: I think that one of the most \nstriking parts about the book,"},{"time":257584,"text":"and in my opinion, one of the reasons it's hit such \na nerve and is resonating around the world,"},{"time":263449,"text":"is that you are personal in the book, \nand that you do make it clear that,"},{"time":269234,"text":"while you've observed some things that are \nvery important for other women to know,"},{"time":273392,"text":"that you've had the same challenges \nthat many others of us have,"},{"time":277951,"text":"as you faced the hurdles and the barriers and \npossibly the people who don't believe the same."},{"time":284746,"text":"So talk about that process: deciding \nyou'd go public with the private part,"},{"time":289384,"text":"and then you would also put yourself in \nthe position of something of an expert"},{"time":293101,"text":"on how to resolve those challenges."}]},{"cues":[{"time":296542,"text":"SS: After I did the TED Talk, what happened was --"},{"time":298726,"text":"you know, I never really expected to write \na book, I'm not an author, I'm not a writer,"},{"time":302474,"text":"and it was viewed a lot, and it really \nstarted impacting people's lives."},{"time":307143,"text":"I got this great --- one of the first \nletters I got was from a woman"},{"time":310663,"text":"who said that she was offered a really big \npromotion at work, and she turned it down,"},{"time":315789,"text":"and she told her best friend she turned \nit down, and her best friend said,"},{"time":318142,"text":"you really need to watch this TED Talk."},{"time":319975,"text":"And so she watched this TED Talk, and she \nwent back the next day, she took the job,"},{"time":324391,"text":"she went home, and she handed her \nhusband the grocery list. (Laughter)"},{"time":329239,"text":"And she said, I can do this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":330831,"text":"And what really mattered to me -- it wasn't \nonly women in the corporate world,"},{"time":333984,"text":"even though I did hear from a lot of \nthem, and it did impact a lot of them,"},{"time":336954,"text":"it was also people of all different circumstances."},{"time":340784,"text":"There was a doctor I met who was an \nattending physician at Johns Hopkins,"},{"time":344531,"text":"and he said that until he saw my TED \nTalk, it never really occurred to him"},{"time":348124,"text":"that even though half the students in \nhis med school classes were women,"},{"time":350498,"text":"they weren't speaking as much as \nthe men as he did his rounds."},{"time":353409,"text":"So he started paying attention, and as he waited for \nraised hands, he realized the men's hands were up."},{"time":359635,"text":"So he started encouraging the \nwomen to raise their hands more,"},{"time":361920,"text":"and it still didn't work."},{"time":363197,"text":"So he told everyone, no more \nhand raising, I'm cold-calling."},{"time":366751,"text":"So he could call evenly on men and women. \nAnd what he proved to himself was that"},{"time":370955,"text":"the women knew the answers just as well or better,"},{"time":373588,"text":"and he was able to go back \nto them and tell them that."},{"time":375476,"text":"And then there was the woman, stay-at-home \nmom, lives in a really difficult neighborhood,"},{"time":380595,"text":"with not a great school, she said that TED \nTalk -- she's never had a corporate job,"},{"time":384631,"text":"but that TED Talk inspired her to go to her school \nand fight for a better teacher for her child."},{"time":390406,"text":"And I guess it was part of was finding my own voice."},{"time":394698,"text":"And I realized that other women and \nmen could find their voice through it,"},{"time":398752,"text":"which is why I went from the talk to the book."}]},{"cues":[{"time":401474,"text":"PM: And in the book, you not only found your \nvoice, which is clear and strong in the book,"},{"time":407799,"text":"but you also share what you've learned --"},{"time":411363,"text":"the experiences of other people in the lessons."},{"time":414506,"text":"And that's what I'm thinking about \nin terms of putting yourself in a --"},{"time":418688,"text":"you became a sort of expert in how you lean in."},{"time":423642,"text":"So what did that feel like, and \nbecome like in your life?\n"},{"time":428034,"text":"To launch not just a book, not just \na best-selling, best-viewed talk,"},{"time":434246,"text":"but a movement, where people began to \nliterally describe their actions at work as,"},{"time":440090,"text":"I'm leaning in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":442772,"text":"SS: I mean, I'm grateful, I'm honored, \nI'm happy, and it's the very beginning."},{"time":449986,"text":"So I don't know if I'm an expert, or if anyone is \nan expert. I certainly have done a lot of research."},{"time":454500,"text":"I have read every study, I have \npored over the materials,"},{"time":457713,"text":"and the lessons are very clear. \nBecause here's what we know:"},{"time":461341,"text":"What we know is that stereotypes are holding women \nback from leadership roles all over the world."},{"time":466053,"text":"It's so striking. \"Lean In\" is very global, \nI've been all over the world,"},{"time":468656,"text":"talking about it, and -- cultures are so different."},{"time":471051,"text":"Even within our own country, to Japan, \nto Korea, to China, to Asia, Europe,"},{"time":476044,"text":"they're so different. Except for one thing: gender."},{"time":480231,"text":"All over the world, no matter what our cultures are,"},{"time":482151,"text":"we think men should be strong, \nassertive, aggressive, have voice;"},{"time":486481,"text":"we think women should speak \nwhen spoken to, help others."}]},{"cues":[{"time":490998,"text":"Now we have, all over the world,"},{"time":494703,"text":"women are called \"bossy.\" \nThere is a word for \"bossy,\""},{"time":498496,"text":"for little girls, in every language there's one."},{"time":500814,"text":"It's a word that's pretty much not used for little boys,"},{"time":503024,"text":"because if a little boy leads, \nthere's no negative word for it,"},{"time":505952,"text":"it's expected. But if a little girl leads, she's bossy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":510741,"text":"Now I know there aren't a lot of \nmen here, but bear with me."},{"time":512736,"text":"If you're a man, you'll have \nto represent your gender."},{"time":515270,"text":"Please raise your hand if you've been \ntold you're too aggressive at work."},{"time":520834,"text":"(Laughter) There's always a few, it runs about \nfive percent. Okay, get ready, gentlemen."},{"time":526718,"text":"If you're a woman, please raise your hand if you've \never been told you're too aggressive at work."},{"time":533281,"text":"(Laughter) That is what audiences have \nsaid in every country in the world,"},{"time":536894,"text":"and it's deeply supported by the data."}]},{"cues":[{"time":539760,"text":"Now, do we think women are more \naggressive than men? Of course not."},{"time":544099,"text":"It's just that we judge them through a different lens,"},{"time":546449,"text":"and a lot of the character traits that you must \nexhibit to perform at work, to get results, to lead,"},{"time":551300,"text":"are ones that we think, in a man, he's a boss,"},{"time":554164,"text":"and in a woman, she's bossy."},{"time":555786,"text":"And the good news about this is that we \ncan change this by acknowledging it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":559872,"text":"One of the happiest moments \nI had in this whole journey is,"},{"time":562262,"text":"after the book came out, I stood on a stage \nwith John Chambers, the CEO of Cisco."},{"time":567195,"text":"He read the book. He stood on a stage with me, he \ninvited me in front of his whole management team,"},{"time":570854,"text":"men and women, and he said, I thought we \nwere good at this. I thought I was good at this."},{"time":574246,"text":"And then I read this book, and I \nrealized that we -- my company --"},{"time":579312,"text":"we have called all of our \nsenior women too aggressive,"},{"time":581296,"text":"and I'm standing on this stage, and I'm sorry."},{"time":583745,"text":"And I want you to know we're \nnever going to do it again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":587490,"text":"PM: Can we send that to a lot of other \npeople that we know? (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":590874,"text":"SS: And so John is doing that because \nhe believes it's good for his company,"},{"time":594775,"text":"and so this kind of acknowledgement \nof these biases can change it."},{"time":597829,"text":"And so next time you all see \nsomeone call a little girl \"bossy,\""},{"time":601477,"text":"you walk right up to that person, \nbig smile, and you say,"},{"time":604025,"text":"\"That little girl's not bossy. That little girl has \nexecutive leadership skills.\" (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":610560,"text":"PM: I know that's what you're telling your daughter. \nSS: Absolutely."}]},{"cues":[{"time":613765,"text":"PM: And you did focus in the book -- and \nthe reason, as you said, in writing it,"},{"time":616834,"text":"was to create a dialogue about this."},{"time":618759,"text":"I mean, let's just put it out there, \nface the fact that women are --"},{"time":622273,"text":"in a time when we have more open \ndoors, and more opportunities --"},{"time":625948,"text":"are still not getting to the leadership positions."},{"time":629248,"text":"So in the months that have come since the book,"},{"time":631446,"text":"in which \"Lean In\" focused on that and said,"},{"time":634004,"text":"here are some of the challenges that remain, and \nmany of them we have to own within ourselves"},{"time":638304,"text":"and look at ourselves. What has changed?"},{"time":641066,"text":"Have you seen changes?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":643152,"text":"SS: Well, there's certainly more \ndialogue, which is great."},{"time":645415,"text":"But what really matters to me, \nand I think all of us, is action."},{"time":648463,"text":"So everywhere I go, CEOs, \nthey're mostly men, say to me,"},{"time":652247,"text":"you're costing me so much money"},{"time":654866,"text":"because all the women want to \nbe paid as much as the men."},{"time":658038,"text":"And to them I say, I'm not sorry at all. (Laughter)"},{"time":662319,"text":"At all. I mean, the women should \nbe paid as much as the men."}]},{"cues":[{"time":665557,"text":"Everywhere I go, women tell me they ask for raises."},{"time":668694,"text":"Everywhere I go, women say they're getting \nbetter relationships with their spouses,"},{"time":672691,"text":"asking for more help at home, asking for the \npromotions they should be getting at work,"},{"time":676671,"text":"and importantly, believing it \nthemselves. Even little things."},{"time":679669,"text":"One of the governors of one of the states told me \nthat he didn't realize that more women were, in fact,"},{"time":683701,"text":"literally sitting on the side \nof the room, which they are,"},{"time":685930,"text":"and now he made a rule that all the women \non his staff need to sit at the table."}]},{"cues":[{"time":691417,"text":"The foundation I started along \nwith the book \"Lean In\""},{"time":693573,"text":"helps women, or men, start circles -- small groups,"},{"time":696925,"text":"it can be 10, it can be however many \nyou want, which meet once a month."},{"time":700174,"text":"I would have hoped that by now, we'd have \nabout 500 circles. That would've been great."},{"time":703495,"text":"You know, 500 times roughly 10."},{"time":706417,"text":"There are over 12,000 circles \nin 50 countries in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":709647,"text":"PM: Wow, that's amazing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":711207,"text":"SS: And these are people who \nare meeting every single month."},{"time":714282,"text":"I met one of them, I was in Beijing."},{"time":716621,"text":"A group of women, they're all about 29 or 30, \nthey started the first Lean In circle in Beijing,"},{"time":721321,"text":"several of them grew up in very poor, rural China."},{"time":725314,"text":"These women are 29, they are told by \ntheir society that they are \"left over,\""},{"time":731122,"text":"because they are not yet married,"},{"time":733135,"text":"and the process of coming together \nonce a month at a meeting"},{"time":735918,"text":"is helping them define who they are for themselves."},{"time":739218,"text":"What they want in their careers. The \nkind of partners they want, if at all."},{"time":743554,"text":"I looked at them, we went around \nand introduced ourselves,"},{"time":745541,"text":"and they all said their names \nand where they're from,"},{"time":747380,"text":"and I said, I'm Sheryl Sandberg, \nand this was my dream."},{"time":750860,"text":"And I kind of just started crying."},{"time":752700,"text":"Right, which, I admit, I do. Right? \nI've talked about it before."},{"time":757457,"text":"But the fact that a woman so far away out in \nthe world, who grew up in a rural village,"},{"time":762027,"text":"who's being told to marry someone \nshe doesn't want to marry,"},{"time":766138,"text":"can now go meet once a month with \na group of people and refuse that,"},{"time":769075,"text":"and find life on her own terms."},{"time":772069,"text":"That's the kind of change we have to hope for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":774012,"text":"PM: Have you been surprised by \nthe global nature of the message?\n"},{"time":777559,"text":"Because I think when the book first \ncame out, many people thought,"},{"time":780864,"text":"well, this is a really important handbook \nfor young women on their way up."},{"time":784616,"text":"They need to look at this, anticipate \nthe barriers, and recognize them,"},{"time":788930,"text":"put them out in the open, have the dialogue about it,"},{"time":791580,"text":"but that it's really for women who are that. \nDoing that. Pursuing the corporate world."},{"time":796699,"text":"And yet the book is being read, as you \nsay, in rural and developing countries."},{"time":801082,"text":"What part of that has surprised you, and \nperhaps led to a new perspective on your part?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":808359,"text":"SS: The book is about self-confidence, \nand about equality."},{"time":811515,"text":"And it turns out, everywhere in the world, \nwomen need more self-confidence,"},{"time":815415,"text":"because the world tells us we're not equal to men."},{"time":817636,"text":"Everywhere in the world, we live in \na world where the men get \"and,\""},{"time":821049,"text":"and women get \"or.\""},{"time":822360,"text":"I've never met a man who's been \nasked how he does it all. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":826034,"text":"Again, I'm going to turn to the men in the audience:"},{"time":829247,"text":"Please raise your hand if you've \nbeen asked, how do you do it all?"},{"time":832279,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":833728,"text":"Men only."},{"time":835159,"text":"Women, women. Please raise your hand \nif you've been asked how you do it all?"},{"time":840037,"text":"We assume men can do it all, \nslash -- have jobs and children."},{"time":846396,"text":"We assume women can't, and that's ridiculous,"},{"time":848174,"text":"because the great majority of women everywhere \nin the world, including the United States,"},{"time":851750,"text":"work full time and have children."}]},{"cues":[{"time":854046,"text":"And I think people don't fully understand \nhow broad the message is."},{"time":859218,"text":"There is a circle that's been started \nfor rescued sex workers in Miami."},{"time":863580,"text":"They're using \"Lean In\" to help \npeople make the transition"},{"time":868931,"text":"back to what would be a fair life, really rescuing \nthem from their pimps, and using it."},{"time":873672,"text":"There are dress-for-success groups \nin Texas which are using the book,"},{"time":877421,"text":"for women who have never been to college."},{"time":879080,"text":"And we know there are groups \nall the way to Ethiopia."},{"time":883008,"text":"And so these messages of equality -- of how women \nare told they can't have what men can have --"},{"time":888891,"text":"how we assume that leadership is for men, \nhow we assume that voice is for men,"},{"time":893124,"text":"these affect all of us, and I \nthink they are very universal."},{"time":896262,"text":"And it's part of what TEDWomen does."},{"time":897923,"text":"It unites all of us in a cause we have to believe in,"},{"time":901706,"text":"which is more women, more voice, more equality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":905954,"text":"PM: If you were invited now to \nmake another TEDWomen talk,"},{"time":912735,"text":"what would you say that is a result \nof this experience, for you personally,"},{"time":918029,"text":"and what you've learned about women, and men,"},{"time":920648,"text":"as you've made this journey?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":924334,"text":"SS: I think I would say -- I tried to say this strongly,"},{"time":927432,"text":"but I think I can say it more strongly --"},{"time":929886,"text":"I want to say that the status quo is not enough."},{"time":933290,"text":"That it's not good enough, that it's \nnot changing quickly enough."},{"time":936270,"text":"Since I gave my TED Talk and published my book, \nanother year of data came out from the U.S. Census."},{"time":941397,"text":"And you know what we found?"},{"time":943186,"text":"No movement in the wage gap \nfor women in the United States."},{"time":945963,"text":"Seventy-seven cents to the dollar."},{"time":948509,"text":"If you are a black woman, 64 cents."},{"time":950543,"text":"If you are a Latina, we're at 54 cents."},{"time":953051,"text":"Do you know when the last \ntime those numbers went up?"},{"time":955479,"text":"2002."},{"time":959786,"text":"We are stagnating, we are \nstagnating in so many ways."},{"time":962670,"text":"And I think we are not really being honest about that,"},{"time":965478,"text":"for so many reasons. It's so \nhard to talk about gender."},{"time":968724,"text":"We shy away from the word \"feminist,\" \na word I really think we need to embrace."},{"time":972541,"text":"We have to get rid of the \nword bossy and bring back --"},{"time":975733,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":978893,"text":"I think I would say in a louder voice, \nwe need to get rid of the word \"bossy\""},{"time":983215,"text":"and bring back the word \"feminist,\" \nbecause we need it."},{"time":986276,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":987761,"text":"PM: And we all need to do a lot more leaning in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":990803,"text":"SS: A lot more leaning in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":992004,"text":"PM: Thank you, Sheryl."},{"time":993234,"text":"Thanks for leaning in and saying yes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":994468,"text":"SS: Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":996630,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}